name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $identifier
desc: Returns: Unique instance identifiers assigned to a device by the software, manufacturers, other organizations or owners. For example: handle ID.

name: $addidentifier
desc: Unique instance identifiers assigned to a device by the software, manufacturers, other organizations or owners. For example: handle ID.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Unique instance identifiers assigned to a device by the software, manufacturers, other organizations or owners. For example: handle ID.

name: $udiDeviceIdentifier
desc: Returns: Unique device identifier (UDI) assigned to device label or package.  Note that the Device may include multiple udiCarriers as it either may include just the udiCarrier for the jurisdiction it is sold, or for multiple jurisdictions it could have been sold.

name: $addudiDeviceIdentifier
desc: Unique device identifier (UDI) assigned to device label or package.  Note that the Device may include multiple udiCarriers as it either may include just the udiCarrier for the jurisdiction it is sold, or for multiple jurisdictions it could have been sold.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Unique device identifier (UDI) assigned to device label or package.  Note that the Device may include multiple udiCarriers as it either may include just the udiCarrier for the jurisdiction it is sold, or for multiple jurisdictions it could have been sold.

name: $deviceName
desc: Returns: A name given to the device to identify it.

name: $adddeviceName
desc: A name given to the device to identify it.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: A name given to the device to identify it.

name: $modelNumber
desc: Returns: The model number for the device.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The model number for the device.

name: $::type
desc: Returns: What kind of device or device system this is.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: What kind of device or device system this is.

name: $specialization
desc: Returns: The capabilities supported on a  device, the standards to which the device conforms for a particular purpose, and used for the communication.

name: $addspecialization
desc: The capabilities supported on a  device, the standards to which the device conforms for a particular purpose, and used for the communication.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: The capabilities supported on a  device, the standards to which the device conforms for a particular purpose, and used for the communication.

name: $::version
desc: Returns: The available versions of the device, e.g., software versions.

name: $addversion
desc: The available versions of the device, e.g., software versions.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The available versions of the device, e.g., software versions.

name: $safety
desc: Returns: Safety characteristics of the device.

name: $addsafety
desc: Safety characteristics of the device.

name: $shelfLifeStorage
desc: Returns: Shelf Life and storage information.

name: $addshelfLifeStorage
desc: Shelf Life and storage information.

name: $physicalCharacteristics
desc: Returns: Dimensions, color etc.

name: $languageCode
desc: Returns: Language code for the human-readable text strings produced by the device (all supported).

name: $addlanguageCode
desc: Language code for the human-readable text strings produced by the device (all supported).

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Language code for the human-readable text strings produced by the device (all supported).

name: $capability
desc: Returns: Device capabilities.

name: $addcapability
desc: Device capabilities.

name: $property
desc: Returns: The actual configuration settings of a device as it actually operates, e.g., regulation status, time properties.

name: $addproperty
desc: The actual configuration settings of a device as it actually operates, e.g., regulation status, time properties.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: The actual configuration settings of a device as it actually operates, e.g., regulation status, time properties.

name: $owner
desc: Returns: An organization that is responsible for the provision and ongoing maintenance of the device.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: An organization that is responsible for the provision and ongoing maintenance of the device.

name: $contact
desc: Returns: Contact details for an organization or a particular human that is responsible for the device.

name: $addcontact
desc: Contact details for an organization or a particular human that is responsible for the device.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Contact details for an organization or a particular human that is responsible for the device.

name: $url
desc: Returns: A network address on which the device may be contacted directly.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A network address on which the device may be contacted directly.

name: $onlineInformation
desc: Returns: Access to on-line information about the device.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: Access to on-line information about the device.

name: $note
desc: Returns: Descriptive information, usage information or implantation information that is not captured in an existing element.

name: $addnote
desc: Descriptive information, usage information or implantation information that is not captured in an existing element.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: Descriptive information, usage information or implantation information that is not captured in an existing element.

name: $quantity
desc: Returns: The quantity of the device present in the packaging (e.g. the number of devices present in a pack, or the number of devices in the same package of the medicinal product).

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The quantity of the device present in the packaging (e.g. the number of devices present in a pack, or the number of devices in the same package of the medicinal product).

name: $parentDevice
desc: Returns: The parent device it can be part of.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The parent device it can be part of.

name: $material
desc: Returns: A substance used to create the material(s) of which the device is made.

name: $addmaterial
desc: A substance used to create the material(s) of which the device is made.

lvardefs.name: objRef
lvardefs.desc: A substance used to create the material(s) of which the device is made.
